        "text": "New product design and development is more often than not a crucial factor in the survival of a company. In a global industrial landscape that is changing fast, firms must continually revise their design and range of products. This is necessary as well due to the fierce competition and the evolving preferences of consumers. Without an R&D program, a firm must rely on [[strategic alliance]]s, [[acquisitions]], and networks to tap into the innovations of others - [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Research_And_Development#Background wikipedia]"
